## 7. Level / Room System (Tiled)

- Levels defined in `LEVEL_NAME`: `WORLD`, `DUNGEON_1`
- Each level has a Tiled JSON tilemap loaded under `ASSET_KEYS[`${level}_LEVEL`]`
- **Rooms** are rectangles on the `rooms` object layer; each has an `id` property
- **Doors** connect rooms. Key Tiled properties: `id`, `targetDoorId`, `targetRoomId`, `targetLevel`, `doorType`, `direction`
- `doorType` values: `OPEN | LOCK | TRAP | BOSS | OPEN_ENTRANCE`
- `trapDoorTrigger` values: `NONE | ENEMIES_DEFEATED | SWITCH | BOSS_DEFEATED`
- `#objectsByRoomId` in `GameScene` maps `roomId → { doors, doorMap, chests, chestMap, pots, switches, enemyGroup, room }`
- Room objects are made **visible/active** only when the player enters that room (`#showObjectsInRoomById`)

