## 10. Spell System

### Architecture

```
SpellCastingComponent (on Player)
  ├── #spellSlots: SpellSlot[]  (indexed 0, 1)
  ├── #spellGroup: Phaser.GameObjects.Group  ← colliders are registered against this
  └── castSpell(slotIndex, casterX, casterY, targetX, targetY) → ActiveSpell | undefined
```

Slot 0 is context-sensitive: casts `FireBolt` when element=FIRE, `EarthBolt` when element=EARTH.  
Slot 1 casts `FireArea` regardless of element.

`EarthWall` and `FireBreath` bypass `SpellCastingComponent` — they are handled directly in `GameScene`:
- `#updateEarthWallSpell()`: key 3 + EARTH element → spawns `EarthWallPillar` objects into `#earthWallGroup`
- `#updateFireBreathChanneling()`: hold Z + FIRE element → creates/updates `FireBreath` instance

### Spell classes (all in `src/game-objects/spells/`)

| Class | Type | Element | Key details |
|---|---|---|---|
| `FireBolt` | Projectile | FIRE | Explodes on hit; triggers FireArea combo |
| `FireArea` | AoE pool | FIRE | Periodic damage; reacts to FireBolt/FireBreath hits |
| `FireBreath` | Channeled | FIRE | Held Z; drains mana per tick; cone detection |
| `EarthBolt` | Projectile | EARTH | Like FireBolt but slower/heavier; triggers LavaPool combo |
| `EarthWallPillar` | Static barrier | EARTH | Has HP; blocks enemies; destroyed on death anim |
| `EarthFireExplosion` | Combo AoE | FIRE+EARTH | Spawned when EarthBolt hits FireArea |
| `LavaPool` | Combo AoE | FIRE+EARTH | Spawned when FireArea+EarthBolt overlap |

### Combos (tracked in GameScene)

| Combo | Trigger | Result |
|---|---|---|
| FireBolt → FireArea | FireBolt overlaps FireArea | FireArea enters "boosted" state (more damage, bigger, faster) |
| FireBreath → FireArea | FireBreath cone covers FireArea | FireArea enters "boosted" combo state |
| EarthBolt → FireArea | EarthBolt hits FireArea | Spawns `EarthFireExplosion` |
| EarthBolt + FireArea overlap | Ongoing overlap | Spawns `LavaPool` |

Active combo tracking: `#activeFireAreaOverlapsByBolt: Map<FireBolt, Set<FireArea>>` and `#activeFireBreathAreaCombos: Set<FireArea>`.

