## 13. Common Patterns & Conventions

### Components
All components extend `BaseGameObjectComponent`. They receive the owning `GameObject` in their constructor. Access the owner via `this.gameObject`.

### Phaser Group cleanup (IMPORTANT)
`Phaser.GameObjects.Group` created via `scene.add.group()` registers its own `SHUTDOWN` listener that calls `group.destroy()` (sets `children = undefined`) **before** manually-registered `SHUTDOWN` handlers.  
**Never call `group.clear()` or `group.destroy()` in your own `SHUTDOWN` handler** — Phaser already cleans up the group, and doing so will crash with `Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'size')`.

### Physics bodies
- `isArcadePhysicsBody(body)` — utility guard from `utils.ts`
- All enemy/player bodies are dynamic `Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Body`
- `EarthWallPillar` body is immovable static — set `body.enable = false` when playing death anim

### Tiled object parsing
Use helpers from `tiled/tiled-utils.ts` — do not read Tiled object layers manually.

### Asset keys
All keys are in `ASSET_KEYS` (from `common/assets.ts`). Level assets follow pattern `${LEVEL_NAME}_LEVEL`, `${LEVEL_NAME}_BACKGROUND`, `${LEVEL_NAME}_FOREGROUND`.

### TypeScript
Private fields use `#` syntax (ES2022 private class fields), not `private` keyword.  
`exhaustiveGuard(x)` in `utils.ts` ensures switch statements are exhaustive.

